 The hypothesis 'but that is unfair for all other children', 

00:01:06.215 --> 00:01:09.255
 Look, first of all you can't be everyone's best friend. 

00:01:09.255 --> 00:01:10.625
 Because then 

00:01:10.725 --> 00:01:13.725
 maybe there are 1 billion children, so every child gets 1 second. 

00:01:13.725 --> 00:01:16.715
 And that is not a very deep relationship. So, 

00:01:16.715 --> 00:01:19.805
 the idea that you can be just as good with everyone, 

00:01:20.495 --> 00:01:23.475
 that is impossible. But even worse, the thing is, 

00:01:23.475 --> 00:01:26.345
 The thing the child does is actually them 

00:01:26.595 --> 00:01:29.365
 they step out of their own self-centeredness, 

00:01:29.365 --> 00:01:32.325
 because their best friend becomes more important than they are. 

00:01:32.325 --> 00:01:34.725
 And that is a precursor to an adult relationship 

00:01:34.725 --> 00:01:37.545
 in which, if you are married, your partner 

00:01:37.545 --> 00:01:40.135
 at least as important as you and the relationship should be 

00:01:40.135 --> 00:01:42.885
 should be even more important. But then you have children 

00:01:42.885 --> 00:01:45.845
 and they are more important than you are. That's a fact. 

00:01:45.845 --> 00:01:48.405
 Unless there is something wrong with you. You come second 

00:01:48.405 --> 00:01:50.105
 and your children come first. 

00:01:50.105 --> 00:01:52.335
 And then very first, I mean * stutter * 

00:01:52.335 --> 00:01:55.205
 you are important because without you they can't do anything, so 

00:01:55.205 --> 00:01:58.455
 you have to take care of yourself. You are no longer first when you have children. 

00:01:58.455 --> 00:02:01.805
 Unless, seriously, you haven't learned the lessons from the playground. 

00:02:02.005 --> 00:02:04.875
 And when you have a best friend you are not first, but they are. 

